  "response": "The characters in *Friends* each have their own quirks and moments of silliness, so it\u2019s subjective to label any one as \"the most stupid.\" However, **Joey Tribbiani** is often portrayed as the least book-smart and most naive of the group. His childlike innocence, frequent misunderstandings, and struggles with basic concepts (like his infamous \"Joey doesn\u2019t share food!\" moment) make him a contender for the \"silliest\" or \"least intellectually inclined\" character. That said, his charm and loyalty make him a beloved part of the show.\n\nOther characters, like **Phoebe Buffay**, also have their moments of absurdity, but hers often stem from her eccentric worldview rather than lack of intelligence. It\u2019s all part of what makes the show so endearing!",
